5:
I hope you get another chance to
live among us and see who we
really are.
9: Still as na√Øve as ever, I see.
13: So what? This is who I am.
17: Then we'll just leave it at that.
21:
I believe you asked me a question.
You wanted to know why I'm a hero,
no?
28:
I never forgot, at least as far as I'm
concerned. All I want is to fight for
what's right.
30:
But perhaps... I forgot the reason
behind that commitment.
34:
I'll ask you one more time, Nate. Why
are you a hero?
38: I just don't want anyone getting hurt.
41:
I like seeing people happy. That
goes for the strong... and the weak.
46:
And... I believe everyone feels that
way deep down. At least a little.
49:
I also think there are bad people
who are strong BECAUSE of what
they've been through. It might not
be true for everyone, but definitely
some.
52:
From my viewpoint, you fit that
description perfectly.
57:
Yeah, probably. I may not have
much confidence, but I've still got a
little of that light in me.
60:
So anyone who wants to stomp out
that light will have to answer to me.
That goes for anyone who throws it
away too.
64:
I want to protect that spark that
lives in us all... Even if I do get jealous
of how bright others shine
sometimes.
68: I see... I think I finally understand you.
72:
Nice work out there, hero... You really
saved me.
82:
Ugh, it's so small! So dirty! So OUT OF
STYLE! Reminds me of my old
troubleshooter days!
85:
Oh? I thought you picked this place
out yourself?
90:
Well, the company suffered a major
loss, after all. Take a look at these
stock prices.
97: You noticed, eh? I knew you would.
101:
The stock prices of PBC, Lunus, and
several others took a severe blow.
Which, given the circumstances,
makes sense.
104:
But AltMeme and Noxel Group's
prices remain the same. How's that
possible?
111:
Indeed it has. The incident with DAN
didn't even put a dent in Noxel's
prices.
115: Regis... Do you believe in gods?
120:
The gods died a long time ago, at
least on my world... But perhaps they
still exist here.
127:
At last, it's finally mine! Thanks for
going shopping with me, Alk!
130:
No problem. I'm just glad it was
worth the wait for you.
133:
So what did you buy? It must be
pretty neat for so many people to
line up for it.
137:
Remember how that motorcycle of
yours is based on a comic book?
This is the complete collector's
edition.
140:
They even included notes on the
world and the artist's novel draft. I
HAD to have it!
143:
Gotcha. Sounds like it's catered to
the super fans.
148:
Speaking of merchandise, looks like
they're selling stuff with you on it too.
162:
You didn't see anything, got it?
Definitely not my fan comic.
166:
Hm? What a coincidence running
into you two.
175:
Well, that's no way to greet a fellow
hero.
183:
Today's my day off. I know some
new merchandise of mine launched
today, so I thought I'd stop by.
187:
Is that why you're here? How nice.
Would you like me to autograph it
for you?
192: AS IF! I'm just hanging out with Alk!
196:
...Why would she hang out with you
and not me?
206:
What's with you? Didn't know you
were the jealous type.
211:
Adults have their fair share of
secrets. Especially if they happen to
be heroes.
215:
Good day to you, Nate! Have I got
news for you!
222:
Ugh, save it. I know it's work! Where
am I going?
228:
It seems to be right around the
corner.
232:
Then let's finish this up quick! I want
to actually ENJOY my day off!
243:
All right, everybody who wants a
knuckle sandwich, get in line!
